B040C001V001	40	1	1	The History of Jesus Christ, Son of David, Son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham begot Isaac. Isaac begot Jacob. Jacob begot Judah and his brothers.
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah had Pharez and Zarah by Tamar. Pharez begot Ezrom. Ezrom begot Aram.
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Aram begot Aminidab. Aminidab begot Nashon. Nashon begot Salmon.
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon had Boaz by Rahab. Boaz had Obed by Ruth. Obed begot Jesse.
B040C001V006	40	1	6	Jesse begot David the king. David the king had Solomon, by her who had been the wife of Uriah.
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon begot Rehoboam. Rehoboam begot Abia. Abia begot Asa.
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa begot Jehoshaphat. Jehoshaphat begot Joram. Joram begot Uzziah.
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah begot Jotham. Jotham begot Ahaz. Ahaz begot Hezekiah.
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah begot Manasseh. Manasseh begot Amon. Amon begot Josiah.
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah had Jeconiah and his brothers, about the time of the migration into Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	After the migration into Babylon, Jeconiah begot Salathiel. Salathiel begot Zerubbabel.
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel begot Abiud. Abiud begot Eliakim. Eliakim begot Azor.
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor begot Zadoc. Zadoc begot Achim. Achim begot Eliud.
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud begot Eleazar. Eleazar begot Matthan. Matthan begot Jacob.
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jacob begot Joseph, the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen; from David till the migration into Babylon, fourteen; from David till the migration into Babylon to the Messiah, fourteen.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ happened thus: Mary his mother had been espoused to Joseph; but before they came together, she proved to be with child by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Joseph her husband being a virtuous man, and unwilling to expose her, intended to divorce her privately.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while he was thinking upon this, an angel of the Lord appearing to him in a dream, said, Joseph, son of David, scruple not to take home Mary your wife; for her pregnancy is from the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	And she shall bear a son, whom you shall call Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.
B040C001V022	40	1	22	In all this what the Lord had spoken by the Prophet was verified,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	«Behold the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, who shall be called Immanuel;» 'which signifies, God with us.'
B040C001V024	40	1	24	When Joseph awoke, he did as the messenger of the Lord had commanded him, and took home his wife;
B040C001V025	40	1	25	but knew her not, until she had brought forth her first born son, whom he named Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	After the birth of Jesus, at Bethlehem of Judea, in the reign of King Herod, certain eastern magicians came to Jerusalem, and inquired,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	Where is the new-born King of the Jews; for we have seen his star in the east country, and are coming to do him homage?
B040C002V003	40	2	3	King Herod hearing this, was alarmed, and all Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	And having assembled all the chief priests and the scribes of the people, he demanded of them where the Messiah should be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	They answered, at Bethlehem of Judea, for thus it is written by the Prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	«And thou Bethlehem, in the canton of Judah, are not the least illustrious among the cities of Judah; for out of thee shall come a ruler, who will govern my people Israel.»
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod having secretly called the magicians, procured from them exact information concerning the time of the star's appearing.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	And sending them to Bethlehem, he said, Go, make an exact inquiry about the child; and when you have found him bring me word, that I may go also, and pay him homage.
B040C002V009	40	2	9	Having heard the King, they departed; and lo! the star which had appeared to them in the east country, moved before them, till it came, and stood over the place, where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	When they again saw the star, they rejoiced exceedingly.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And being come into the house, they found the child with Mary his mother; and, prostrating themselves, did him homage. Then opening their caskets, they offered, as presents to him, gold, frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And being warned in a dream not to return to Herod, they went home another way.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	When they were gone, lo! a messenger of the Lord appearing to Joseph in a dream, said, Arise, take the child with his mother, and flee into Egypt; and remain there till I order you; for Herod will seek the child to destroy him.
B040C002V014	40	2	14	Accordingly he arose, took the child with his mother, and withdrew by night into Egypt,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	«where he continued until the death of Herod; so that, what the Lord had spoken by the Prophet, was verified,» 'Out of Egypt I called my Son.'
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, finding that he had been deceived by the magicians, was highly incensed and dispatched emissaries who slew, by his order, all the male children in Bethlehem, and in all its territory, from those entering the second year, down to the time of which he had procured exact information from the magicians.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was the word of Jeremiah the Prophet verified,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	«A cry was heard in Ramah, lamentation, and weeping, and bitter complaint: Rachel bewailing her children, and refusing to be comforted, because they are no more.»
B040C002V019	40	2	19	When Herod was dead, an angel of the Lord appearing in a dream to Joseph in Egypt, said,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	Arise, take the child with his mother, and go into the land of Israel; for they are dead who sought his life.
B040C002V021	40	2	21	Accordingly, he arose, took the child with his mother, and came to the land of Israel;
B040C002V022	40	2	22	but hearing that Archelaus had succeeded his father Herod in the throne of Judea, he was afraid to return thither; and being warned in a dream, retired into the district of Galilee,
B040C002V023	40	2	23	and resided in a city named Nazareth; in this verifying the declarations of the Prophet concerning Jesus, that he should be called a Nazarene.
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In those days appeared John the Immerser, who proclaimed in the wilderness of Judea, saying,
B040C003V002	40	3	2	Reform, for the Reign of Heaven approaches.
B040C003V003	40	3	3	«For this is he, of whom the Prophet Isaiah speaks in these words,» 'The voice of one proclaiming in the wilderness, Prepare a way for the Lord, make for him a straight passage.'
B040C003V004	40	3	4	Now John wore raiment of camel's hair with a letter girdle about his waist; and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then Jerusalem, and all Judea, and all the country along the Jordan, resorted to him,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were immersed by him in the Jordan, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But he seeing many Pharisees and Sadducees coming to him to receive immersion, said to them, Offspring of vipers, who has prompted you to flee from the impending vengeance?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Produce, then, the proper fruit of reformation;
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and presume not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham for our father, for I assure you, that of these stones God can raise children to Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	And even now the ax lies at the root of the trees; every tree, therefore, which produces not good fruit, is cut down, and turned into fuel.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I, indeed, immerse you in water, into reformation; but he who comes after me, is mightier than I, whose shoes I am not worthy to carry. He will immerse you in the Holy Spirit, and in fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing shovel is in his hand, and he will thoroughly cleanse his grain; he will gather his wheat into the granary, and consume the chaff in unquenchable fire.
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then came Jesus from Galilee to the Jordan, to be immersed by John.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John excused himself, saying, It is I who need to be immersed by you; and you come to me!
B040C003V015	40	3	15	Jesus answering, said to him, 
B040C003V016	40	3	16	Jesus being immersed, no sooner arose out of the water, than heaven was opened to him; and the Spirit of God appeared, descending like a dove, and lighting upon him;
B040C003V017	40	3	17	while a voice from heaven proclaimed, This is my Son, the beloved, in whom I delight.
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then was Jesus conducted by the Spirit into the wilderness, to be tempted by the devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And after fasting forty days and forty nights, he was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	Then the tempter accosting him, said, If thou be God's Son, command that these stones become loaves.
B040C004V004	40	4	4	«Jesus answering, said, 
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil conveyed him into the holy city, and having placed him on the battlement of the temple,
B040C004V006	40	4	6	«said to him, If thou be God's Son, throw thyself down; for it is written,» 'He will give his angels the charge of thee: they shall uphold thee in their arms, lest thou dash thy foot against a stone.'
B040C004V007	40	4	7	«Jesus again answered, 
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again the devil took him up a very high mountain, whence he showed him all the kingdoms of the world in their glory,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and said to him, All these will I give thee, if thou wilt prostrate thyself, and worship me.
B040C004V010	40	4	10	«Jesus answered, 
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil leaving him, angels came and ministered to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now Jesus, hearing that John was imprisoned, retired into Galilee,
B040C004V013	40	4	13	and having left Nazareth, resided at Capernaum, a seaport in the confines of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	thereby verifying the words of Isaiah the Prophet;
B040C004V015	40	4	15	«The canton of Zebulun and the canton of Naphtali, situate on the Jordan near the sea, Galilee of the nations;»
B040C004V016	40	4	16	the people who abode in darkness, saw a great light, and on those who inhabited a region of the shades of death, light has arisen.
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time Jesus began to proclaim, saying, 
B040C004V018	40	4	18	Then walking by the sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon named Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a drag into the sea, for they were fishers.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	And he said to them, 
B040C004V020	40	4	20	Immediately they left the nets and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	Passing on he saw other two brothers, James the son of Zebedee and John his brother, in the bark with their father Zebedee, mending their nets, and he called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	They immediately, leaving the bark and their father, followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	Then Jesus went over all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, and proclaiming the glad tidings of the Reign, and curing every sort of disease and malady among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And his fame spread through all Syria, and they brought him all their sick, seized and tormented with various distempers, demoniacs, and lunatics, and paralytics, and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And vast multitudes followed him from Galilee, Decapolis, Jerusalem, Judea, and from the banks of the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	Jesus, seeing so great a confluence, repaired to a mountain, and having sat down, his disciples came to him.
B040C005V002	40	5	2	Then breaking silence, he taught them, saying:
