B040C007V028	40	7	28	When Jesus had ended this discourse, the people were struck with awe at his manner of teaching;
B040C007V029	40	7	29	for he taught as one who had authority, and not as the Scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	Being come down from the mountain, followed by a great multitude,
B040C008V002	40	8	2	a leper came, who, presenting himself before him, said, Sir, if you will, you can cleanse me.
B040C008V003	40	8	3	Jesus stretched out his hand, and touched him, saying, 
B040C008V004	40	8	4	Then Jesus said to him, 
B040C008V005	40	8	5	Having entered Capernaum, a centurion accosted him with this request,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	Sir, my man-servant lies sick at home, exceedingly afflicted with a palsy.
B040C008V007	40	8	7	Jesus answered, 
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion replying, said, Sir, I am not worthy, that you should come under my roof; only say the word, and my servant will be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For even I, who am under command myself, having soldiers under me, say to one, Go, and he goes; to another, Come, and he comes; and to my servant, Do this, and he does it.
B040C008V010	40	8	10	Jesus hearing this, was astonished, and said to those who followed, 
B040C008V011	40	8	11	
        
B040C008V012	40	8	12	
        
B040C008V013	40	8	13	Then Jesus said to the centurion, 
B040C008V014	40	8	14	Then Jesus having entered Peter's house, saw his wife's mother lying sick of a fever,
B040C008V015	40	8	15	and having touched her hand, the fever left her; on which she arose and entertained him.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	In the evening they presented to him many demoniacs; and he expelled the spirits with a word, and cured all the sick;
B040C008V017	40	8	17	«thus verifying the saying of the Prophet Isaiah,» 'He has himself carried off our infirmities, and borne our distresses.'
B040C008V018	40	8	18	Jesus seeing himself crowded on all sides, gave orders to pass to the opposite shore.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	Meantime, a scribe accosted him, saying, Rabbi, I will follow you whithersoever you go.
B040C008V020	40	8	20	Jesus answered, 
B040C008V021	40	8	21	Another, one of his disciples, said to him, Master, permit me to go first, and bury my father.
B040C008V022	40	8	22	Jesus answered, 
B040C008V023	40	8	23	Then entering the bark, his disciples followed him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	Soon after there arose in the sea so great a tempest, that the bark was covered with billows. But he being asleep,
B040C008V025	40	8	25	the disciples came and waked him, saying, Save us, Master, we perish.
B040C008V026	40	8	26	He answered, 
B040C008V027	40	8	27	insomuch that every one exclaimed with admiration, What personage is this, whom even the winds and the sea obey.
B040C008V028	40	8	28	When he was come to the other side, into the country of the Gadarenes, there met him two demoniacs, issuing out of the monuments, so furious, that no person durst pass that way.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	These instantly cried, saying, What hast thou to do with us, Son of God? Art thou come hither to torment us before the time?
B040C008V030	40	8	30	Now there was feeding, at some distance, a great herd of swine.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	And the friends besought him, saying, If thou expel us, permit us to go into the herd of swine.
B040C008V032	40	8	32	He answered, 
B040C008V033	40	8	33	Then the herdsmen fled into the city, and reported everything, and what had happened to the demoniacs.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	Presently the whole city went out to meet Jesus, and having seen him, entreated him to depart out of their territory.
B040C009V001	40	9	1	Then having gone aboard the bark, he repassed, and went to his own city;
B040C009V002	40	9	2	where they brought to him a paralytic, laid upon a bed. Jesus perceiving their faith, said to the paralytic, 
B040C009V003	40	9	3	On which some of the scribes said within themselves, This man blasphemes.
B040C009V004	40	9	4	But Jesus knowing their sentiments, said, 
B040C009V005	40	9	5	
        
B040C009V006	40	9	6	
        
B040C009V007	40	9	7	Accordingly he arose, and went home.
B040C009V008	40	9	8	And the people saw and wondered, glorifying God, who had given such power to men.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	As Jesus departed thence, he saw a man, named Matthew, sitting at the toll office; to whom he said, 
B040C009V010	40	9	10	Afterward Jesus being at table in a house, many publicans and sinners came, and placed themselves with him and his disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	Some of the Pharisees observing this, said to his disciples, Why does your teacher eat with publicans and sinners?
B040C009V012	40	9	12	Jesus hearing them, answered, 
B040C009V013	40	9	13	«
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then John's disciples addressing him, said, We and the Pharisees often fast: why do your disciples never fast?
B040C009V015	40	9	15	Jesus answered, 
B040C009V016	40	9	16	
        
B040C009V017	40	9	17	
        
B040C009V018	40	9	18	While he was speaking, a ruler came, and prostrating himself, said, My daughter is by this time dead; but come, and lay your hand upon her, and she will revive.
B040C009V019	40	9	19	And Jesus arose, and, as he followed him, with his disciples,
B040C009V020	40	9	20	a woman, who had been twelve years afflicted with a bloody issue, coming behind, touched the tuft of his mantle;
B040C009V021	40	9	21	for she said within herself, If I but touch his mantle, I shall recover.
B040C009V022	40	9	22	Jesus turning about, saw her, and said, 
B040C009V023	40	9	23	Being come into the ruler's house, and seeing the players on the flute, with the crowd, making a bustle,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	he said to them, 
B040C009V025	40	9	25	but when the people were put out, he entered, and having taken her by the hand, the young woman arose.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	Now the fame of this action spread through all the country.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	When Jesus departed thence, two blind men followed him, crying, Son of David, have pity upon us.
B040C009V028	40	9	28	Being come into the house, the blind men approached him: and Jesus said to them, 
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then he touched their eyes, saying, 
B040C009V030	40	9	30	Immediately their eyes were opened. And Jesus strictly charging them, said, 
B040C009V031	40	9	31	But being departed, they spread his fame through all that country.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	They were scarcely gone, when a dumb demoniac was presented to him.
