B041C015V023	41	15	23	where they gave him wine to drink, mingled with myrrh, which he would not receive.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	When they had nailed him to the cross, they parted his garments, dividing by lot what every man should take.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	Now it was the third hour, when they nailed him to the cross.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And the inscription, bearing the cause of his death, was in these words, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	They likewise crucified two robbers with him, one at his right hand, and the other at his left.
B041C015V028	41	15	28	«And the scripture was fulfilled, which says,» 'He was ranked with malefactors.'
B041C015V029	41	15	29	Meanwhile, they who passed by reviled him, shaking their heads, and saying, Ah! you who could demolish the temple, and rebuild it in three days!
B041C015V030	41	15	30	save yourself, and come down from the cross!
B041C015V031	41	15	31	The chief priests likewise, with the scribes, deriding him, said among themselves, He saved others; can not he save himself?
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let the Messiah, the King of Israel, descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe! Even those who were crucified with him reproached him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	Now from the sixth hour until the ninth, darkness covered all the land.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	At the ninth hour, Jesus cried aloud saying, 
B041C015V035	41	15	35	Some who were present, hearing this, said, Hark! he calls Elijah.
B041C015V036	41	15	36	One at the same time ran, and dipped a sponge in vinegar, and having fastened it to a stick, presented it to him to drink, saying, Let alone, we shall see whether Elijah will come to take him down.
B041C015V037	41	15	37	And Jesus sending forth a cry expired.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	Then was the vail of the temple rent in two, from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	And the centurion who stood opposite observing that he expired with so loud a cry, said, Surely, this man was a son of a god.
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were women also looking on at a distance, amongst whom were Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the younger, and of Joses and Salome,
B041C015V041	41	15	41	(these had followed him, and served him, when he was in Galilee,) and several others, who came with him to Jerusalem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	When it was evening, (because it was the preparation, that is, the eve of the Sabbath,)
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathea, an honorable senator, who himself also expected the Reign of God, taking courage, repaired to Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	Pilate, amazed that he was so soon dead, sent for the centurion, and asked him whether Jesus had been dead any time.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	And being informed by the centurion, he granted the body to Joseph;
B041C015V046	41	15	46	who having bought linen, and taking Jesus down, wrapped him in the linen; and laid him in a tomb, hewn out of the rock.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	Now Mary the Magdalene, and Mary the mother of Joses, saw where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	When the Sabbath was past, Mary the Magdalene, Mary the mother of James, and Salome, bought spices that they might embalm Jesus.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And early in the morning, the first day of the week, they came to the tomb about sunrise.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	And they said among themselves, Who will roll away the stone for us from the entrance of the tomb? (for it was very large.)
B041C016V004	41	16	4	But when they looked, they saw that the stone had been rolled away.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	Then entering the tomb, they beheld a youth sitting on the right side, clothed in a white robe, and they were frightened.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, Be not frightened; you seek Jesus the Nazarene, who was crucified. He is risen, he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go, say to his disciples, and to Peter, He is gone before you to Galilee; where you shall see him, as he told you.
B041C016V008	41	16	8	The women then getting out, fled from the tomb, seized with trembling and consternation; but said nothing to any one, they were so terrified.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	Jesus having arisen early the first day of the week, appeared first to Mary the Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven demons.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	She went and informed those who had attended him, who were in affliction and tears.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	But when they heard that he was alive, and had been seen by her, they did not believe it.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	Afterward he appeared in another form to two of them, as they traveled on foot into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	These being returned, informed the other disciples, but neither did they believe him.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	At length he appeared to the eleven, as they were eating, and reproached them with their incredulity and obstinacy, in disbelieving those who had seen him after his resurrection.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And he said unto them, 
B041C016V016	41	16	16	
        
B041C016V017	41	16	17	
        
B041C016V018	41	16	18	
        
B041C016V019	41	16	19	Now, after the Lord had spoken to them, he was taken up into heaven, and sat down at the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	As for them, they went out and proclaimed the tidings everywhere, the Lord co-operating with them, and confirming their doctrine by the miracles with which it was accompanied.
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Forasmuch as many have undertaken to compose a narrative of those things, which have been accomplished amongst us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	as they, who were from the beginning, eye-witnesses, and afterwards ministers of the word, delivered them to us;
B042C001V003	42	1	3	I have also determined, having exactly traced everything from the first, to write a particular account for you, most excellent Theophilus;
B042C001V004	42	1	4	that you might know the certainty of those matters wherein you have been instructed.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	In the days of Herod, king of Judea, there was a priest named Zacharias, of the course of Abijah; and his wife, named Elizabeth, was of the daughters of Aaron.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	They were both righteous before God, blameless observers of all the Lord's commandments and ordinances.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	And they had no child, because Elizabeth was barren, and they were advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	Now when he came to officiate as priest in the order of his course,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	it fell to him by lot, according to the custom of the priesthood, to offer incense in the sanctuary.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And while the incense was burning, the whole congregation were praying without.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	Then there appeared to him an angel of the Lord, standing on the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And Zacharias was discomposed at the sight, and in great terror.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, Fear not, Zacharias; for your prayer is heard, and Elizabeth your wife shall bear you a son, whom you shall name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	He shall be to you matter of joy and transport; and many shall rejoice because of his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he shall be great before the Lord; he shall not drink wine nor any fermented liquor; but he shall be filled with the Holy Spirit, even from his mother's womb.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And many of the sons of Israel he shall bring back to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	Moreover, he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elijah, to reconcile fathers to their children, and by the wisdom of the righteous, to render the disobedient a people well disposed for the Lord.
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zacharias said to the angel, How shall I know this: for I am old man, and my wife is advanced in years?
B042C001V019	42	1	19	The angel answering, said to him, I am Gabriel, who attend in the presence of God, and am sent to tell you this joyful news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	But know that you shall be dumb, and shall not recover your speech, till the day when these things happen, because you have not believed my words, which shall be fulfilled in due time.
B042C001V021	42	1	21	Meanwhile the people waited for Zacharias, and wondered that he staid so long in the sanctuary.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	But when he came out, he could not speak to them; and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the sanctuary; for he made them understand by signs, and remained speechless.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And when his days of officiating were expired, he returned home.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	Soon after, Elizabeth his wife conceived, and lived in retirement five months, and said,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	The Lord has done this for me, purposing now to deliver me from the reproach I lay under among men.
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Now, in the sixth month, God sent Gabriel his angel, to Nazareth, a city of Galilee;
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a virgin betrothed to a man called Joseph, of the house of David, and the virgin's name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	When the angel entered, he said to her, Hail, favorite of heaven! the Lord be with you, happiest of women!
B042C001V029	42	1	29	At his appearance and words, she was perplexed, and revolved in her mind what this salutation could mean.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	And the angel said to her, Fear not, Mary, for you have found favor with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And behold, you shall conceive and bear a son, whom you shall name Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest. And the Lord God will give him the throne of David his Father.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And he shall reign over the house of Jacob forever: his reign shall never end.
B042C001V034	42	1	34	Then said Mary to the angel, How shall this be, since I have no intercourse with man?
B042C001V035	42	1	35	The angel answering, said to her, The Holy Spirit will descend upon you, and the power of the Highest will overshadow you; therefore the holy progeny shall be called the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And lo! your cousin Elizabeth also has conceived, a son in her old age; and she who is called barren, is now in her sixth month;
B042C001V037	42	1	37	for nothing is impossible with God.
B042C001V038	42	1	38	And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord. Be it to me according to your word. Then the angel departed.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	In those days Mary set out, and traveled expeditiously into the hill country; to a city of Judah;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	where having entered the house of Zacharias, she saluted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	As soon as Elizabeth heard Mary's salutation, the babe leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit,
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and cried with a loud voice, You are the most blessed of women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb.
B042C001V043	42	1	43	But how have I deserved this honor, to be visited by the mother of my Lord!
B042C001V044	42	1	44	for know, that as soon as the sound of your salutation reached my ears, the babe leaped in my womb for joy.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And happy is she who believed that the things which the Lord has promised her, shall be performed.
B042C001V046	42	1	46	Then Mary said, My soul magnifies the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	and my spirit rejoices in God my Saviour;
B042C001V048	42	1	48	because he has not disdained the low condition of his handmaid; for henceforth, all posterity will pronounce me happy.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	For the Almighty, whose name is venerable, has done wonders for me.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	His mercy on them who fear him, extends to generations of generations.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He displays the strength of his arm, and dispels the vain imaginations of the proud.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He pulls down potentates from their thrones, and exalts the lowly.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	The needy he loads with benefits; but the rich he spoils of everything.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He supports Israel his servant, ever inclined to mercy,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	(as he promised to our fathers) toward Abraham and his race.
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mary, after staying with Elizabeth about three months, returned home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	When the time for Elizabeth's delivery was come, she brought forth a son;
B042C001V058	42	1	58	and her neighbors and relations who heard that the Lord had shown her great kindness, rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And, on the eighth day, when they came to the circumcision of the child, they would have called him by his father's name, Zacharias.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	And his mother interposed, saying, No; but he shall be called John.
B042C001V061	42	1	61	They said to her, There is none of your kindred of that name.
B042C001V062	42	1	62	They, therefore, asked his father by signs, how he would have him called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	He, having demanded a table-book, wrote upon it, His name is John, which surprised them all.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	And his mouth was opened directly, and his tongue loosed. And he spoke, praising God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	Now all in the neighborhood were struck with awe; and the fame of these things spread throughout all the hill country of Judea.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all who heard these things, pondering them in their hearts, said, What will this child hereafter be? And the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	Then Zacharias, his father, being filled with the Holy Spirit, prophesied, saying,
B042C001V068	42	1	68	Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, because he has visited and redeemed his people;
B042C001V069	42	1	69	and has raised a Prince for our deliverance in the house of David his servant;
B042C001V070	42	1	70	(as anciently he promised by his holy prophets)
B042C001V071	42	1	71	for our deliverance from our enemies, and from the hands of all who hate us;
B042C001V072	42	1	72	in kindness to our forefathers, and remembrance of his holy institution;
B042C001V073	42	1	73	the oath which he swore to our father Abraham,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	to grant to us, that being rescued out of the hands of our enemies, we might serve him boldly,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	in piety and uprightness all our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, shall be called a prophet of the Most High; for you shall go before the Lord, to prepare his way,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	by giving the knowledge of salvation to his people, in the remission of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	through the tender compassion of our God, who has caused a light to spring from on high to visit us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	to enlighten those who abide in darkness and in the shades of death; to direct our feet into the way of peace.
B042C001V080	42	1	80	Meantime the child grew, and acquired strength of mind, and continued in the deserts, until the time when he made himself known to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	About that time, Cesar Augustus issued an edict, that all the inhabitants of the empire should be registered.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	(This first register took effect, when Cyrenius was president of Syria.)
B042C002V003	42	2	3	When all went to be registered, every one of his own city,
B042C002V004	42	2	4	Joseph also went from Nazareth, a city of Galilee, to a city of David in Judea, called Bethlehem, (for he was of the house and lineage of David,)
B042C002V005	42	2	5	to be registered, with Mary, his betrothed wife, who was pregnant.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	While they were there, the time came, that she should be delivered.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she brought forth her first born son, and swathed him, and laid him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the house allotted to strangers.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	Now there were shepherds in the fields in that country, who tended their flocks by turns through the night watches.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	On a sudden, an angel of the Lord stood by them, and a divine glory encompassed them with light, and they were frightened exceedingly.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	But the angel said to them, Fear not; for lo! I bring you good tidings, which shall prove matter of great joy to all the people;
B042C002V011	42	2	11	because today is born to you in the city of David, a Saviour, who is the Lord Messiah.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And by this you shall know him; you shall find a babe in swaddling bands, lying in a manger.
B042C002V013	42	2	13	Instantly the angel was attended by a multitude of the heavenly host, who praised God, saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	Glory to God in the highest heaven, and on earth peace, and good will amongst men!
B042C002V015	42	2	15	And when the angels returned to heaven, having left the shepherds, these said to one another, Let us go to Bethlehem, and see this which has happened, of which the Lord has informed us.
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And hastening thither, they found Mary and Joseph with the babe, who lay in the manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	When they saw this, they published what had been imparted to them, concerning this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all who heard it, wondered at the things told them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary let none of these things escape unobserved, weighing every circumstance within herself.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God, for all that they had heard and seen, agreeably to what had been declared to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	On the eighth day, when the child was circumcised, they called him Jesus, the angel having given him that name, before his mother conceived him.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when the time of their purification was expired, they carried him to Jerusalem, as the law of Moses appoints, to present him to the Lord;
B042C002V023	42	2	23	«(as it is written in the law of God,'Every male, who is the first born of his mother, is consecrated to the Lord:')»
B042C002V024	42	2	24	and to offer the sacrifices enjoined in the law, a pair of turtle doves, or two young pigeons.
B042C002V025	42	2	25	Now there was at Jerusalem a man named Simeon, a just and religious man, who expected the consolation of Israel; and the Holy Spirit was upon him,
B042C002V026	42	2	26	and had revealed to him, that he should not dies, until he had seen the Lord's Messiah.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	This man came, guided by the Spirit, into the temple. And when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him what the law required,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	he took him into his arms, and blessed God, and said,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	Now, Lord, thou dost in peace dismiss thy servant, according to thy word;
B042C002V030	42	2	30	for my eyes have seen the Saviour,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	whom thou hast provided in the sight of all the world,
B042C002V032	42	2	32	a luminary to enlighten the nations, and to be the glory of Israel thy people.
B042C002V033	42	2	33	And Joseph, and the mother of Jesus heard, with admiration, the things spoken concerning him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	And Simeon blessed them, and said to Mary his mother, This child is destined for the fall and the rise of many in Israel, to serve as a mark for contradiction;
B042C002V035	42	2	35	(yes, you own soul shall be pierced as with a javelin;) that the thoughts of many hearts may be disclosed.
B042C002V036	42	2	36	There was also a prophetess, Anna, daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher, in advanced age, who had lived seven years with a husband, whom she married when a virgin;
B042C002V037	42	2	37	and being now a widow about eighty-four years, departed not from the temple, but served God in prayer and fasting night and day;
B042C002V038	42	2	38	she also coming in at that instant, gave thanks to the Lord, and spoke concerning Jesus to all those in Jerusalem who expected redemption.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	After they had performed everything required by the law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee, to their own city Nazareth.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	And the child grew, and acquired strength of mind, being filled with wisdom, and adorned with a divine gracefulness.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	Now, the parents of Jesus went yearly to Jerusalem at the feast of the passover.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	And when he was twelve years old, they having gone thither, according to the usage of the festival, and remained the customary time;
B042C002V043	42	2	43	being on their return, the child Jesus staid behind in Jerusalem, and neither Joseph nor his mother knew it.
B042C002V044	42	2	44	They supposing him to be in the company, went a day's journey, and then sought him among their relations and acquaintances;
B042C002V045	42	2	45	but not finding him, they returned to Jerusalem, seeking him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	And after three days they found him in the temple, sitting among the doctors, both hearing them, and asking them questions.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	And all who heard him, were amazed at his understanding and answers,
B042C002V048	42	2	48	and they beheld him with astonishment. And his mother said to him, Son, why have you treated us thus? Behold, your father and I have sought you with sorrow.
B042C002V049	42	2	49	He answered, 
B042C002V050	42	2	50	But they did not comprehend his answer.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	And he returned with them to Nazareth, and was subject to them. And his mother treasured up all these things in her memory.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	And Jesus advanced in wisdom, and stature, and in power with God and man.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius, Pontius Pilate being procurator of Judea, Herod tetrarch of Galilee, Philip, his brother, tetrarch of Iturea, and the province of Trachonitis, and Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene;
B042C003V002	42	3	2	in the high priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, the word of God came to John the son of Zacharias, in the wilderness.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	And he went through all the country along the Jordan, publishing the immersion of reformation for the remission of sins.
B042C003V004	42	3	4	«As it is written in the book of the prophet Isaiah,» 'The voice of one proclaiming in the wilderness, Prepare a way for the Lord, make for him a straight passage.'
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Let every valley be filled, every mountain and hill be leveled; let the crooked roads be made straight, and the rough ways smooth,
B042C003V006	42	3	6	«that all flesh may see the salvation of God.»
B042C003V007	42	3	7	Then said he to the multitudes, who flocked out to be immersed by him, Offspring of vipers, who has prompted you to flee from the impending vengeance?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Produce, then, the proper fruits of reformation; and say not within yourselves, We have Abraham for a father; for I assure you, that of these stones God can raise children to Abraham.
B042C003V009	42	3	9	And even now the ax lies at the root of the trees. Every tree, therefore, which produces not good fruit, is cut down, and thrown into the fire.
B042C003V010	42	3	10	Upon this, the multitude asked him, What must we do then?
B042C003V011	42	3	11	He answered, Let him who has two coats, impart to him who has none; and let him who has victuals do the same.
B042C003V012	42	3	12	There came also publicans to be immersed, who said, Rabbi, what must we do?
B042C003V013	42	3	13	He answered, Exact no more than what is appointed you.
B042C003V014	42	3	14	Soldiers likewise asked him, And what must we do? He answered, Injure no man, either by violence, or false accusation, and be content with your allowance.
B042C003V015	42	3	15	As the people were in suspense concerning John, every man imagining within himself that he might be the Messiah,
B042C003V016	42	3	16	John addressed them all, saying, I, indeed, immerse in water; but one mightier than I comes, whose shoe-latchet I am not worthy to untie; he will immerse you in the Holy Spirit and fire;
B042C003V017	42	3	17	his winnowing shovel is in his hand, and he will thoroughly cleanse his grain; he will gather the wheat into his granary, and consume the chaff in unquenchable fire.
B042C003V018	42	3	18	And with many other exhortations, he published the good tidings to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	But Herod, the tetrarch, having been reproved by him, on account of Herodias, his brother's wife, and for all the crimes which Herod had committed,
B042C003V020	42	3	20	added this to the number, that he confined John in prison.
B042C003V021	42	3	21	Now when John immersed all the people, Jesus was likewise immersed; and while he prayed, the heaven was opened,
B042C003V022	42	3	22	and the Holy Spirit descended upon him in a bodily form, like a dove; and a voice came from heaven, which said, Thou art my Son, the beloved; in thee I delight.
B042C003V023	42	3	23	Now Jesus was himself about thirty years in subjection, being (as was supposed) a son of Joseph, son of Heli,
B042C003V024	42	3	24	son of Matthat, son of Levi, son of Melchi, son of Janna, son of Joseph,
B042C003V025	42	3	25	son of Mattathias, son of Amos, son of Nahum, son of Esli, son of Naggai,
B042C003V026	42	3	26	son of Maath, son of Mattathias, son of Shimei, son of Joseph, son of Judah,
B042C003V027	42	3	27	son of Joanna, son of Reza, son of Zerubbabel, son of Salathiel, son of Neri,
B042C003V028	42	3	28	son of Melchi, son of Addi, son of Cosam, son of Elmodam, son of Er,
B042C003V029	42	3	29	son of Joses, son of Eliezer, son of Jorim, son of Matthat, son of Levi,
