B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	This was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things were made by him, and without him not a single creature was made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and the life was the light of man.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shone in darkness, but the darkness received it not.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	A man named John, was sent from God.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	This man came as a witness, to testify concerning the light, that through him, all might believe.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not himself the light; but came to testify concerning the light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	The true light was he who, coming into the world, enlightens every man.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world was made by him; yet the world knew him not.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own land, and his own people did not receive him;
B043C001V012	43	1	12	but to as many as received him, believing in his name, he granted the privilege of being children of God;
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who derive their birth not from blood, nor from the desire of the flesh, nor from the will of man, but from God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word became incarnate, and sojourned amongst us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of favor and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	(It was concerning him John testified, when he cried, This is He of whom I said, He that comes after me, is preferred to me; for he was before me.)
B043C001V016	43	1	16	Of his fulness we all have received, even favor for favor's sake;
B043C001V017	43	1	17	for the law was given by Moses-the favor and the truth came by Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one ever saw God; it is the only begotten Son, who is in the bosom of the Father, who has made him known.
