B044C003V011	44	3	11	And while he kept fast hold of Peter and John, all the people ran together to them, exceedingly astonished, in the portico called Solomon's.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	And Peter, seeing this, answered the people, Israelites, why do you wonder at this? or why do you fix your eyes on us, as if by our own power, or piety, we had made this man to walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, has glorified his Son Jesus, whom you delivered up, and rejected in the presence of Pilate, when he was desirous to release him:
B044C003V014	44	3	14	but you rejected the Holy and Righteous One, and desired a murderer to be granted to you;
B044C003V015	44	3	15	and killed the Prince of Life, whom God has raised from the dead, of which we are witnesses;
B044C003V016	44	3	16	and his name, through faith in his name, has made this man strong, whom ye see and know; yes, the faith which is by him, has given him this perfect soundness, in the presence of you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	And now, brethren, I know that through ignorance you did it, as did also your rulers;
B044C003V018	44	3	18	but those things which God foretold, by the mouth of all his prophets, that the Messiah should suffer, he has thus fulfilled.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Reform, therefore, and return to God, that so your sins may be blotted out; that seasons of refreshment may come from the presence of the Lord,
B044C003V020	44	3	20	and that he may send Jesus Christ, who was before designed for you:
B044C003V021	44	3	21	whom, indeed, heaven must retain till the time of the accomplishment of all things, which God has spoken by the mouth of all his holy prophets, from the beginning of time.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	«Moses truly said, to the fathers,» 'A prophet like me shall the Lord your God raise up for you, from among your brethren; him shall you obey in all things, whatsoever he shall say to you:'
B044C003V023	44	3	23	«and it shall come to pass, that every soul who will not obey that prophet, shall be cut off from among the people.»
B044C003V024	44	3	24	Yes, and all the prophets from Samuel, and those that succeeded, as many as have spoken, have also foretold these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	«You are the children of the prophets, and of the institution which God instituted with our fathers, saying to Abraham,» 'And in your see shall all the families of the earth be blessed.'
B044C003V026	44	3	26	To you, first, God, having raised up his Son, has sent him to bless you; in turning every one of you, from your iniquities.
B044C004V001	44	4	1	And while they were speaking to the people, the priests, the captain of the temple guard, and the Sadducees, came upon them;
B044C004V002	44	4	2	being grieved that they taught the people, and announced, through Jesus, the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid hands on them, and committed them into custody to the next day; for it was now evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	But many of those who had heard the word, believed: and the number of the men was about five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	And the next day their rulers, elders, and scribes, gathered together at Jerusalem:
B044C004V006	44	4	6	both Annas, the high priest, and Caiaphas; also John, and Alexander, and as many as were of the high priest's kindred.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And having set them in the midst, they inquired, By what power, or in what name, have you done this?
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, full of the Holy Spirit, said to them, Rulers of the people, and elders of Israel;
B044C004V009	44	4	9	if we are this day examined about the benefit conferred on the impotent man, by what means he is healed;
B044C004V010	44	4	10	be it known to you all, and to all the people of Israel, that through the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God has raised from the dead: yes, by HIM this man stands before you hale.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the stone which was set at nought by you builders, that is become the head of the corner:
B044C004V012	44	4	12	and there is salvation in no other; for there is no other name under heaven given among men, by which we can be saved.
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Now, when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and understood that they were illiterate men, and in private stations in life, they were astonished, and recollected their having been with Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	And seeing the man that was cured standing with them, they had nothing to say against it.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	But having ordered them to withdraw out of the council, they conferred among themselves,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	saying, What shall we do with these men? for that indeed a signal miracle has been wrought by them, is manifest to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem; and we can not deny it.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	Nevertheless, that it may not spread any further among the people, let us charge them, with the severest threats, to speak no more to any man in this name.
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And having called them, they charged them neither to speak nor teach any more in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John, answering them, said, Whether it be just in the sight of God, to obey you rather than God, judge you:
B044C004V020	44	4	20	for we can not but speak the things which we have seen and heard.
B044C004V021	44	4	21	And having threatened them again, they dismissed them, on account of the people, finding nothing for which they might punish them; because all the people glorified God for that which was done;
B044C004V022	44	4	22	for the man on whom this miracle of healing was wrought, was more than forty years old.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And being dismissed, they came to their own company, and related all that the chief priests and elders had said to them.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	And when they heard it, they lifted up their voice with one accord to God, and said, Lord, thou art the God who didst make heaven and earth; and the sea, and all things that are in them:
B044C004V025	44	4	25	«who didst say by the mouth of thy servant David,» 'Why did the heathen rage, and the people imagine vain things?'
B044C004V026	44	4	26	«The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers combined together against the Lord, and against his anointed.»
B044C004V027	44	4	27	For of a truth, against thy holy Son Jesus, whom thou hast anointed, both Herod, and Pontius Pilate, with the heathen, and the people of Israel,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	have combined to do what thy hand and thy counsel marked out before to be done.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	And now, O Lord, regard their threatenings; and give to thy servants to speak thy word with all freedom;
B044C004V030	44	4	30	whilst thou stretchest out thy hand to heal, and signs and wonders are doing through the name of thy holy Son Jesus.
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And while they were praying, the place in which they were assembled was shaken: and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they spoke the word of God with freedom.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	Now the heart and soul of the multitude of believers was one: nor did any one call any of his possessions his own; but all things were common among them.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power did the Apostles give forth their testimony concerning the resurrection of the Lord Jesus: and great kindness was among them all.
B044C004V034	44	4	34	Neither was there one indigent person among them; for as many as were proprietors of lands or houses, sold them, and brought the price of the things they sold,
B044C004V035	44	4	35	and laid it down at the feet of the Apostles: and distribution was made to each according to his need.
B044C004V036	44	4	36	And Joses, who, by the Apostles, was surnamed Barnabas, (which being interpreted, signifies a Son of Exhortation,) a Levite, and by birth a Cyprian,
B044C004V037	44	4	37	having an estate, sold it, and brought the money and laid it down at the feet of the Apostles.
B044C005V001	44	5	1	But a certain man, named Ananias, with Sapphira, his wife, sold an estate,
B044C005V002	44	5	2	and secreted a part of the price, his wife also, being privy to it: and bringing a certain part, he laid it down at the feet of the Apostles.
B044C005V003	44	5	3	But Peter said, Ananias, why has Satan filled your heart, that you should attempt to impose on the Holy Spirit, and to secrete a part of the price of the land?
B044C005V004	44	5	4	While it remained, did it not continue yours? and when it was sold, was it not at your own disposal? Why have you admitted this thing into your heart? You have not lied to men, but to God.
B044C005V005	44	5	5	And Ananias, hearing these words, fell down and expired: and great fear fell on all that heard these things.
B044C005V006	44	5	6	Then the young men arose, and bound him up, and carrying him out, they buried him.
B044C005V007	44	5	7	After the interval of about three hours, his wife, also, not knowing what was done, came in.
B044C005V008	44	5	8	And Peter said to her, Tell me whether you sold the land for so much. And she said, Yes, for so much.
B044C005V009	44	5	9	Then Peter said to her, How is it that you have conspired together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? Behold the feet of those who have been burying your husband are at the door, and they shall carry you out.
