B044C005V011	44	5	11	And great fear came on all the assembly, and on all that heard these things.
B044C005V012	44	5	12	And many signs and wonders were done among the people by the hands of the Apostles, (and they were all unanimously in Solomon's portico;
B044C005V013	44	5	13	and not one of the rest presumed to join himself to them, but the people magnified them:
B044C005V014	44	5	14	and believers were more and more added to the Lord, multitudes both of men and women:)
B044C005V015	44	5	15	insomuch that along the streets they brought out the sick, and laid them on beds, and couches, that even the shadow of Peter, coming by, might overshadow some of them.
B044C005V016	44	5	16	And multitudes also, out of the cities round about, came together to Jerusalem, bringing the sick, and those that were troubled with unclean spirits, who were all healed.
B044C005V017	44	5	17	But the high priest arising, and all they that were him, being the sect of the Sadducees, were filled with zeal,
B044C005V018	44	5	18	and laid their hands on the Apostles, and put them into the common prison.
B044C005V019	44	5	19	But a messenger of the Lord, by night, opened the doors of the prison, and bringing them out, said,
B044C005V020	44	5	20	Go, and presenting yourselves in the temple, speak to the people all the words of this life.
B044C005V021	44	5	21	And hearing this, they went very early into the temple, and taught. But the high priest being come, and they that were with him, they called together the Sanhedrim, even the whole Senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.
B044C005V022	44	5	22	But when the officers came, they found them not in the prison. Returning, therefore, they made their report,
B044C005V023	44	5	23	saying, We found, indeed, the prison shut with all safety, and the keepers standing before the doors; but, having opened them, we found no one within.
B044C005V024	44	5	24	Now, when the high priest, and the captain of the temple guard, and the chief priests heard these words, they doubted concerning them, what this could be.
B044C005V025	44	5	25	But one came, and told them, Behold, the men whom you put in prison, are standing in the temple, and teaching the people.
B044C005V026	44	5	26	Then the captain went, with the officers, and brought them, (not by violence, for they feared the people, lest they should be stoned:)
B044C005V027	44	5	27	and when they had brought them, they set them before the Sanhedrim. And the high priest asked them,
B044C005V028	44	5	28	saying, Did we not strictly charge you, that you should not teach in this name? and behold, you have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and would bring this man's blood upon us.
B044C005V029	44	5	29	But Peter and the other Apostles answered, and said, It is necessary to obey God rather than men.
B044C005V030	44	5	30	The God of our fathers has raised up Jesus, whom you slew, hanging him on a tree:
B044C005V031	44	5	31	HIM has God exalted at his right hand, a Prince and Saviour, to give reformation to Israel, and remission of sins.
B044C005V032	44	5	32	And we are witnesses of these things, and the Holy Spirit also, whom God has given to them who submit to his government.
B044C005V033	44	5	33	And when they heard this, they were enraged, and consulted to put them to death.
B044C005V034	44	5	34	But a certain Pharisee in the Sanhedrim, whose name was Gamaliel, a doctor of law, in great esteem among all the people, rose up, and commanded the Apostles to be taken out for a little while;
B044C005V035	44	5	35	and he said to them, Men of Israel, take heed to yourselves what you are about to do to these men.
B044C005V036	44	5	36	Some time ago Theudas arose, pretending himself to be a person of note: to whom a number of men, about four hundred, adhered, who was slain; and all who hearkened to him were scattered, and came to nothing.
