B044C013V032	44	13	32	And we bring you good tidings, that the very promise which was made to the fathers,
B044C013V033	44	13	33	«God has accomplished to us, their children, in raising up Jesus: as it is also written in the second Psalm,» 'Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee.'
B044C013V034	44	13	34	«And because he has raised him from the dead, no more to return to corruption, he has spoken thus,» 'I will give you the sure mercies of David.'
B044C013V035	44	13	35	«Wherefore, also, in another place he says,» 'Thou wilt not permit thy Holy One to see corruption.'
B044C013V036	44	13	36	Now David, having served his own generation according to the will of God; fell asleep, and was gathered to his fathers, and saw corruption.
