B044C017V018	44	17	18	Then some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers opposed him. Others said, What would this babbler say? And others, he seems to be a proclaimer of foreign deities; because he declared to them the good news concerning Jesus and the resurrection.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And they took him and conducted him to the Areopagus, saying, May we know what this new doctrine is, which is spoken by you?
