B044C018V010	44	18	10	
        
B044C018V011	44	18	11	And he continued there a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	But when Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews made an assault upon Paul, with one consent, and brought him before the tribunal,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	saying, This fellow persuades men to worship God contrary to the law.
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paul would have opened his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews, If it were an act of injustice, or mischievous licentiousness, O Jews! it were reasonable I should bear with you.
B044C018V015	44	18	15	But if it be a question concerning words, and names, and the law which is among you, you see to it yourselves; for I will be no judge of these matters.
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them away from the tribunal.
