B044C019V001	44	19	1	Now it came to pass, that while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul, having passed through the upper parts, came to Ephesus: and finding there some disciples,
B044C019V002	44	19	2	he said to them, Have you, on your believing, received the Holy Spirit? And they replied to him, No; we have not so much as heard whether the Holy Spirit is received.
B044C019V003	44	19	3	And he said to them, Into what, then, were you immersed? And they said, Into John's immersion.
B044C019V004	44	19	4	And Paul said, John, indeed, administered the immersion of reformation, telling the people that they should believe in Him that was to come after him: that is, in Jesus.
B044C019V005	44	19	5	And hearing this, they were immersed into the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And Paul, laying his hands, on them, the Holy Spirit came upon them; and they spoke with tongues, and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	And they were, in all, about twelve men.
