B044C019V025	44	19	25	whom he gathered together, with the workmen employed about the business, and said, Men, you know that our maintenance arises from this manufacture;
B044C019V026	44	19	26	and you see and hear that this Paul has persuaded great numbers of people, not only of Ephesus, but almost of all Asia, and has turned them aside, saying that they are not deities which are made with hands;
B044C019V027	44	19	27	so that there is danger, not only that this occupation of ours should be depreciated, but also that the people of the great goddess Diana should be despised, and her grandeur destroyed; whom all Asia and the world worship.
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And hearing this, they were filled with rage; and cried out, saying, Great is Diana of the Ephesians!
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was filled with confusion; and they rushed with one accord into the theater, dragging thither Gaius and Aristarchus, Macedonians, Paul's fellow-travelers.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	And when Paul would have gone in to the people, the disciples would not permit him.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And some, too, the principal officers of Asia, as they had a friendship for him, sent to him, and desired that he would not venture himself into the theater.
