B044C023V035	44	23	35	I will hear you, said he, when your accusers are also come. And he commanded him to be kept in Herod's praetorium.
B044C024V001	44	24	1	And, after five days, the high, Ananias, came down, with the elders, and a certain orator, named Tertullus: and they made their appearance before the governor, against Paul.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	And he being called, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, As we enjoy great peace by your means, and as illustrious deeds are happily done to this nation, by your prudent administration;
B044C024V003	44	24	3	we accept it always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	But, that I may not further trouble you, I beseech you to hear us briefly, with your usual candor.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	for we have found this man a pestilent fellow, and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world; and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes:
B044C024V006	44	24	6	who has attempted to profane the temple; and whom we apprehended, and would have judged according to our law;
B044C024V007	44	24	7	but Lysias, the commander, coming upon us with a great force, took him away out of our hands,
B044C024V008	44	24	8	commanding his accusers to come to you; by which means, you may yourself, on examination, know the certainty of all these things, of which we accuse him.
B044C024V009	44	24	9	And the Jews also gave their assent, saying, that these things were so.
B044C024V010	44	24	10	Then Paul, after the governor had made a signal to him to speak, answered, Knowing that you, O Felix! have been for several years a judge to this nation, I answer for myself with the more cheerfulness;
B044C024V011	44	24	11	since you may know that it is no more than twelve days since I went up to worship at Jerusalem;
B044C024V012	44	24	12	and they neither found me disputing with any man in the temple, nor making any insurrection among the people, either in the synagogues, or in the city:
B044C024V013	44	24	13	nor can they produce any proof of the things concerning which they now accuse me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	But this I confess to you, that after the way which they call a sect, so worship I the God of our fathers; believing all things which are written in the law, and in the prophets;
B044C024V015	44	24	15	having hope toward God, of that which they themselves also expect, that there shall be a resurrection of the dead, both of the just and of the unjust.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	And upon this account, I exercise myself to have always a conscience without offense toward God, and toward men.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	Now, after several years, I came to bring alms to my nation, and offerings:
