B066C004V001	66	4	1	After these things, I saw, and behold, a door opened in heaven: and the first voice which I heard was as of a trumpet speaking to me; and it said, Come up hither, and I will show you what shall be hereafter.
B066C004V002	66	4	2	And immediately I was in the Spirit: and behold, a throne was set in heaven, and one sitting upon it;
B066C004V003	66	4	3	and he who sat on it, was in appearance like a jasper and sardine stone; and a rainbow, in appearance like an emerald, was round about the throne.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	And round about the throne there were twenty-four thrones; and on the thrones, twenty-four elders sitting, clothed with white apparel; and upon their heads golden crowns.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And out of the throne there came lightnings, and thunders, and voices. And seven lamps of fire were burning before the throne, which are the seven Spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And before the throne there was a sea of glass, like crystal. And in the middle of the throne, in the circle about the throne, there were four living creatures, full of eyes, before and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	And the first creature was like a lion; and the second creature was like a calf; and the third creature had a face like a man; and the fourth creature was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And the four living creatures had, each of them, six wings round about; and within they were full of eyes: and they rest not, day or night, saying, Holy, holy, holy, Lord God Almighty, who wast, and art, and art to come.
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And while the living creatures are giving glory, and honor, and thanks to him who sits upon the throne, who lives for ever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the twenty-four elders fall down before him who sits upon the throne, who lives for ever and ever; and they cast down their crowns before the throne, saying,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	Worthy art thou, O Lord, to receive glory, and honor, and power; for thou hast created all things, and for thy pleasure they are, and were created.
B066C005V001	66	5	1	And I saw in the right hand of him who sat on the throne, a scroll written within and without, sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	And I saw a mighty messenger proclaiming with a great voice, Who is worthy to open the scroll, and to loose its seals?
B066C005V003	66	5	3	And one in heaven, nor upon the earth, nor under the earth, was able to open the scroll, or to look into it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And I wept abundantly, because no one was found worthy to open the scroll, nor to look into it.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	And one of the elders said to me, Weep not; behold the Lion of the tribe of Judah, the Root of David, has prevailed to open the scroll and its seven seals.
B066C005V006	66	5	6	And I beheld, in the middle space, between the throne and the four living creatures, and in the midst of the elders, there stood a Lamb, which seemed to have been slain, having seven horns, and seven eyes; these are the seven Spirits of God, sent forth into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	And he came and took the scroll out of the right hand of him who sat upon the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	And when he received the scroll, the four living creatures, and the twenty-four elders fell down before the Lamb, having every one harps, and golden vials full of perfumes, which are the prayers of the saints.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	And they sung a new song, saying, Worthy art thou to take the scroll, and to open the seals of it; for thou wast slain, and hast redeemed us to God by thy blood, out of every tribe, and language, and people, and nation;
B066C005V010	66	5	10	and hast made us, to our God, kings and priests: and we shall reign on earth.
B066C005V011	66	5	11	And I beheld, and heard the voice of many angels round about the throne, and of the living creatures, and of the elders: and the number of them was myriads of myriads, and thousands of thousands;
B066C005V012	66	5	12	saying, with a loud voice, Worthy is the Lamb that was slain, to receive power and riches, and wisdom, and might, and honor, and glory, and blessing!
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And every creature which is in heaven, and on the earth, and under the earth, and such as are in the sea, even all things that are in them, I heard saying, To him who sits upon the throne, and to the Lamb be blessing, and honor, and glory, and strength, for ever and ever!
B066C005V014	66	5	14	And the four living creatures said, Amen: and the elders fell down and worshiped him.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	And I saw, when the Lamb opened one of the seals; and I heard one of the four living creatures, which said, as with a voice of thunder, Come and see.
B066C006V002	66	6	2	And I saw, and behold, a white horse; and he who sat upon it, had a bow, and there was given him a crown; and he went forth conquering, and to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	And when he opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature, saying, Come-
B066C006V004	66	6	4	And another horse came out, which was red; and it was given to him who sat upon it, to take peace from the earth, and that they should slay each other; and there was given to him a great sword.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	And when he had opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature, saying, Come and see. And I saw, and behold, a black horse; and he who sat upon it, has a pair of scales in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	And I heard a voice in the midst of the four living creatures, saying, A chenix of wheat for a denarius, and three chenices of barley for a denarius; you see that you injure not the oil, nor the wine.
B066C006V007	66	6	7	And when he opened the fourth seal, I heard the voice of the fourth living creature, saying, Come and see.
B066C006V008	66	6	8	And I saw, and behold, a pale horse; and as for him who sat on it, his name was Death; and Hades followed him: and there was given to him power to slay the fourth part of the earth with the sword, and with famine, and with death, and with the wild beasts of the field.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	And when he opened the fifth sea, I saw, under the altar, the souls of those who were slaughtered on account of the word of God, and the testimony which they held.
B066C006V010	66	6	10	And they cried with a loud voice, and said, How long, O sovereign Lord, holy and true, before thou dost judge, and avenge our blood upon those who dwell on the earth?
B066C006V011	66	6	11	And there were given to each of them white robes; and it was said to them, that they should rest yet a while, till the number of their fellow-servants and brethren who should be killed, as they had been, should be completed.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	And I saw, when he opened the sixth seal, and there was an earthquake; and the sun became black as sackcloth of hair; and the moon became as blood;
B066C006V013	66	6	13	and the stars fell from heaven, on the earth, as fig tree drops its untimely figs, being shaken by a mighty wind:
B066C006V014	66	6	14	and the heavens passed away like a scroll, when it is rolled up; and every mountain, and island, was moved out of its place:
B066C006V015	66	6	15	and the kings of the earth, and the grandees, and the rich men, and the chief officers, and the powerful men, and every slave, and every freeman, hid themselves in the caves, and rocks of the mountains:
B066C006V016	66	6	16	and they said to the mountains, and the rocks, Fall on us, and hide us from the face of him who sits on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb!
B066C006V017	66	6	17	for the great day of his wrath is come, and who shall be able to stand?
B066C007V001	66	7	1	And, after these things, I saw four angels, standing at the four corners of the earth, holding the four winds of the earth, that the wind might not blow upon the earth, nor upon the sea, nor on any tree.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	And I saw another angel ascending from the rising sun, having the seal of the living God: and he cried with a great voice to the four angels to whom power was given to injure the earth, and the sea;
B066C007V003	66	7	3	saying, Injure not the earth, nor the sea, nor the trees, till we have sealed the servants of our God, in their foreheads.
B066C007V004	66	7	4	And I heard the number of those that were sealed: one hundred and forty-four thousand, who were sealed out of every tribe of the children of Israel.
B066C007V005	66	7	5	Of the tribe of Judah, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Reuben, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Gad, were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V006	66	7	6	Of the tribe of Asher, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Naphtali, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Manasseh, were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V007	66	7	7	Of the tribe of Simeon, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Levi, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Issachar, were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V008	66	7	8	Of the tribe of Zebulon, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Joseph, were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Benjamin, were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After this, I saw, and beheld a great multitude, which no one could number, out of every nation, and tribe, and people, and language, standing before the throne, and before the Lamb, clothed in white robes, and palms in their hands;
B066C007V010	66	7	10	and they cry with a loud voice, saying, Salvation to our God who sits upon the throne, and to the Lamb!
B066C007V011	66	7	11	And all the messengers stood round about the throne, and about the elders, and the four living creatures; and they fell down on their faces, before the throne, and worshiped God;
B066C007V012	66	7	12	saying, Amen: the blessing, and the glory, and the wisdom, and the thanksgiving, and the honor, and the power, and the strength, be to our God for ever and ever: Amen.
B066C007V013	66	7	13	And one of the elders answered, saying to me, As for those who are clothed with white apparel, who are they, and whence do they come?
B066C007V014	66	7	14	And I said to him, Sir, you know. And he said to me, These are they who have come out of much tribulation, and have washed their robes, and made them white in the blood of the Lamb:
B066C007V015	66	7	15	therefore, they are before the throne of God, and serve him, day and night, in his temple; and he who sits upon the throne, pitches his tabernacle over them.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They shall hunger no more, neither shall they thirst any more; nor shall the sun fall upon them, nor any heat:
B066C007V017	66	7	17	for the Lamb, who is in the midst of the throne, shall feed them, and he shall lead them to fountains of living water; and God shall wipe away every tear from their eyes.
B066C008V001	66	8	1	And when he had opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	And I saw the seven angels which stood before God; and seven trumpets were given to them.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	And another angel came, and stood before the altar, having a golden censer; and there was given to him much incense, that he might present it with the prayers of all the saints, upon the golden altar which was before the throne.
B066C008V004	66	8	4	And the smoke of the perfumes went up, with the prayers of the saints, from the hand of the angel, before God.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	And the angel took the censer, and filled it with the fire of the altar, and threw it upon the earth; and there were voices, and thunders, and lightnings, and an earthquake.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	And the seven angels who had the seven trumpets, prepared themselves to sound.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	And the first sounded; and there hail and fire, mingled with blood, and it was cast down upon the earth; and a third part of the trees was burnt up, and all the herbage was burnt up.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	And the second angel sounded; and it was as if a great mountain, burning with fire, was cast into the sea;
B066C008V009	66	8	9	and a third part of the creatures which had life in the sea, died; and a third part of the ships were destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	And the third angel sounded; and there fell from heaven a great star, blazing like a torch; and fell upon the third part of the rivers, and upon the fountains of waters:
B066C008V011	66	8	11	and the name of the star was called Wormwood, and a third part of the waters became wormwood; and many men died of the waters, because they were become bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	And the fourth angel sounded; and the third part of the sun was smitten, and the third part of the moon, and the third part of the stars, so that the third part of them was darkened, and the day was obscured for a third part, and the night also.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	And I beheld, and heard one of the angels flying in the midst of heaven, saying with a loud voice, Woe, woe, woe, to those who dwell upon the earth, for the remaining sounds of the trumpets of the three angels, which are yet to sound!
B066C009V001	66	9	1	And the fifth angel sounded; and I saw a Star fall from the heaven to the earth; and there was given to him the key of the bottomless pit.
B066C009V002	66	9	2	And he opened the bottomless pit, and smoke ascended from the pit, as the smoke of a great furnace: and the sun and the air were darkened by the smoke of the pit.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	And out of the smoke there came locusts upon the earth; and power was given to them, as scorpions of the earth have power.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	And it was said to them that they should not injure the grass of the earth, nor any green thing, nor any tree; but the men who had not the seal of God in their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	And it was not given to them to kill them, but to torment them five months: and their torment was like that of a scorpion when it stings a man.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	And in these days men shall seek death, and shall not find it: and they shall desire to die, and death shall fly from them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	And the resemblance of the locusts was like horses prepared for war; and on their heads were, as it were, crowns of gold; and their faces were like the faces of men:
B066C009V008	66	9	8	and they had tresses, like the tresses of women; and their teeth were like the teeth of lions.
B066C009V009	66	9	9	And they had breastplates like breastplates of iron; and the noise of their wings was like the noise of chariots, and many horses rushing to war.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	And they had tails like scorpions, and their stings were in their tails; and their power was to hurt men five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	For they had a king over them, the angel of the bottomless pit, whose name, in the Hebrew language, is Abaddon; and in the Greek, he has the name Apollyon.
B066C009V012	66	9	12	One woe is gone, and behold other two woes, besides it, yet coming.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	And the sixth angel sounded; and I heard a voice from the four horns of the golden altar which was before God,
B066C009V014	66	9	14	saying to the sixth angel, who had the trumpet, Loose the four angels who are bound by the great river Euphrates.
B066C009V015	66	9	15	And the four angels were loosed, who were prepared for an hour, and a day, and a month, and a year, to kill a third part of men.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	And the number of the horsemen was two myriads of myriads: I heard the number of them.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	And I saw the horses, and those who sat upon them, thus in their appearance; having breastplates of fire, and hyacinth, and brimstone: and the heads of the horses were like the heads of lions, and out of their mouths went fire, and smoke, and brimstone.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	With these three-by the fire, by the smoke, and by the brimstone-that went out of their mouths, they slew a third part of men.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	And their powers are in their mouths, and in their tails; and their tails are like serpents, having heads, and with them they injure.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	Yet the remainder of men, who died not by these plagues, did not reform from the works of their hands, that they might not worship demons, and idols of gold, and silver, and brass, and stone, and wood; which can neither see, nor hear, nor walk.
B066C009V021	66	9	21	And they reformed not from their murders, and their magical incantations; nor from their fornication, nor their thefts.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	And I saw another mighty angel descending from heaven, clothed with a cloud; and a rainbow was about his head, and his face was as the sun, and his feet like pillars of fire.
B066C010V002	66	10	2	And he had in his hand a little book, open; and he put his right foot upon the sea, and the left upon the earth.
B066C010V003	66	10	3	And he cried out with a loud voice, as when a lion roars: and when he cried, the seven thunders uttered their voices.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	And when the seven thunders had spoken, I was about to write: and I heard a voice from heaven, saying, Seal up what the seven thunders have spoken, and write it not.
B066C010V005	66	10	5	And the angel, whom I saw standing on the sea and on the earth, lifted up his hand toward heaven,
B066C010V006	66	10	6	and swore by him that lives for ever and ever, who created the heaven, and those things which are in it; and the sea, and the things which are in it; and the earth, and the things which are in it; that there should be no longer delay.
B066C010V007	66	10	7	But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel; when he shall begin to sound, then the secret of God, as he had revealed its glad tidings to his servants the prophets, should be fulfilled.
B066C010V008	66	10	8	And the voice which I heard from heaven spoke to me again, and said, Go, take the little book, which is open, out of the hand of the angel which stands upon the sea and upon the earth.
B066C010V009	66	10	9	And I went to the angel, and said to him, Give me the little book. And he said to me, Take it, and eat it up; and it shall embitter your stomach, but in your mouth it shall be as sweet as honey.
B066C010V010	66	10	10	And I took the little book out of the hand of the angel, and eat it up; and in my mouth it was sweet as honey, but when I had eaten it, my stomach was bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	And he said to me, You must again prophesy to many people, and nations, and tongues, and kings.
B066C011V001	66	11	1	And there was given to me a reed like a measuring rod, saying, Arise, and measure the temple of God, and the altar, and those who worship at it;
B066C011V002	66	11	2	and the outer court of the temple throw out, and measure it not; for it shall be given to the Gentiles, and they shall trample upon the holy city forty-two months.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	And I will give to my two witnesses commission, and they shall prophesy a thousand two hundred and sixty days, clothed in sackcloth.
B066C011V004	66	11	4	These are the two olive trees, and the two lamps, which stand before the Lord of the earth.
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if any one will injure them, fire shall come out of their mouth, and devour their enemies: and if any one will injure them, so must he be put to death.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	These have power to shut heaven, so that no rain shall be showered down in the days of their prophecy; they have power over the waters, to turn them to blood, and to smite the earth as often as they will, with every plague.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	And when they shall have finished their testimony, the savage beast which ascends out of the abyss, shall make war against them, and shall conquer them, and kill them.
B066C011V008	66	11	8	And their corpses shall lie in the street of the great city, which is spiritually called Sodom and Egypt; where also our Lord was crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	And persons of various people, and tribes, and tongues, and nations, shall look on their dead bodies three days and a half, and shall not permit their corpses to be laid in the graves.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	And they who dwell upon the earth shall rejoice over them, and be glad, and shall send gifts to each other; because these two prophets tormented those who dwelt upon the earth.
