B066C015V005	66	15	5	And after this I saw, and the temple of the tabernacle of the testimony was opened in heaven;
B066C015V006	66	15	6	and the seven angels who had the seven plagues, came out of the temple, clothed with pure shining linen garments; and were girded round the breasts with golden girdles.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels, seven golden vials, full of the wrath of God, who lives for ever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was full of smoke from the glory of God, and from his power. And no one could enter into the temple till the seven plagues of the seven angels were finished.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	And I heard a great voice out of the temple saying, to the seven angels, Go, and pour out the vials of the wrath of God upon the earth.
B066C016V002	66	16	2	And the first went forth, and poured out his vial upon the earth; and there was a malignant and grievous ulcer upon the men who had the mark of the beast, and upon them who worshiped his image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	And the second angel poured out his vial upon the sea; and it became blood, like that of a dead man: and every living soul that was in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	And the third angel poured out his vial upon the rivers, and on the fountains of water; and they became blood.
