B066C021V002	66	21	2	And I, John, saw the holy city, the New Jerusalem, descending from God, out of heaven, prepared like a bride adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a great voice out of heaven, saying, Behold, the tabernacle of God is with men, and he shall pitch his tent among them, and they shall be his people, and God himself shall be among them-their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	And he shall away wipe every tear from their eyes; and death shall be no more, nor grief, nor crying; nor shall there be any more pain: for the former things are passed away.
B066C021V005	66	21	5	And he that sat upon the throne, said, Behold, I make all things new. And he said, Write, for these are true and faithful words.
B066C021V006	66	21	6	And he said to me, It is done. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the End: I will give to him that is athirst, of the fountain of the water of life freely.
B066C021V007	66	21	7	The conqueror shall inherit all things: and I will be to him a God, and he shall be to me my son.
B066C021V008	66	21	8	But, as for the cowards, and unbelieving, and the abominable, and murderers, and prostitutes, and sorcerers, and idolaters, and all liars-their part shall be in the lake which burns with fire and brimstone, which is the second death.
B066C021V009	66	21	9	And there came one of the seven angels, who had the seven vials full of the seven last plagues; and spoke with me, saying, Come, and I will show you the bride, the Lamb's wife.
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he brought me, in the Spirit, to a great and high mountain; and he showed me the city, the holy Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	having the glory of God; (its luster was like that of a precious gem, even as a jasper stone, clear as crystal,)
B066C021V012	66	21	12	having a great and high wall; having also twelve gates, and over the gates twelve angels, and names written upon them, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the sons of Israel:
B066C021V013	66	21	13	on the east, three gates; on the north, three gates; and on the south, three gates; and on the west, three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations; and on them the names of the twelve Apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he that spoke with me, had a golden reed, that he might measure the city, and its gates and wall.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	And the city is square, and its length is equal to its breadth: and he measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand furlongs: and its length and its breadth, and its height are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured its wall, one hundred and forty-four cubits, according to the measure of a man, that is, of an angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the wall was built of jasper, and the city was pure gold, like refined glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	And the foundations of the walls of the city, were adorned with every precious stone. The first foundation is jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, chalcedony; the fourth, emerald;
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolite; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, topaz; the tenth, chrysoprasus; the eleventh, hyacinth; and the twelfth, amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates were twelve pearls: each of the gates was of one pearl. And the street of the city was pure gold, like transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	And I saw no temple in it, for the Lord God Almighty, and the Lamb, are the temple of it.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	And the city had no need of the sun, neither of the moon, to shine in it; for the glory of the Lord enlightened it, and the Lamb is the light of it.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations of the saved shall walk in its light; and the kings of the earth do bring their glory and their honor into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And the gates of it shall not be shut by day; (for there shall be no night there.)
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and the honor of the nations into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	And nothing unclean shall enter into it, nor anything which practices abomination and falsehood; but only those who are written in the Lamb's book of life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	And he showed me a river of water of life, clear as crystal, issuing out of the throne of God, and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	In the midst of the broad street, and on each side of the river, was the tree of life, producing twelve kinds of fruit- producing its fruit in every month: and the leaves of the tree are for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And every curse shall cease. And the throne of God, and of the Lamb, shall be in it; and his servants shall serve him.
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see his face: and his name shall be borne upon their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And there shall be no more night; and they have no need of a lamp, nor of the light of the sun; because the Lord God shall enlighten them: and they shall reign for ever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said to me, These words are faithful and true. And the Lord God of the holy prophets, has sent his holy angel to show his servants what must quickly be done.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	
        
B066C022V008	66	22	8	And I, John, saw and heard these things, and when I heard and saw them, I fell down to worship before the feet of the angel who showed me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	And he said to me, See you do it not: I am a fellow-servant with you, and of your brethren, the prophets, and of those who keep the words of this book: worship God.
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he said to me, Seal not up the words of the prophecy of this book; for the time is near.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	Let him that is unjust, be unjust still; and let him that is polluted, be polluted still; and let him that is righteous, be righteous still; and let him that is holy, be holy still.
B066C022V012	66	22	12	
        
B066C022V013	66	22	13	
        
B066C022V014	66	22	14	(Happy are they who keep his commandments, that they may have the privilege to eat of the tree of life; and they shall enter by the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	Without are the dogs, and the sorcerers, and the fornicators, and the murderers, and the idolaters, and every one who loves and invents a lie.)
B066C022V016	66	22	16	
        
B066C022V017	66	22	17	And the Spirit and the Bride say, Come: and let him that hears, say, Come: and let him that is thirsty, come: whoever will, let him take of the water of life freely.
B066C022V018	66	22	18	And I testify of every one that hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man add to these things, God shall add to him the plagues which are written in this book:
B066C022V019	66	22	19	and if any one take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God will take away his part out of the book of life, and out of the holy city-the things which are written in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	He who testifies these things, says, 
B066C022V021	66	22	21	May the favor of the Lord Jesus Christ be with all the saints!
